Task: Implement parse_junit_xml() - JUnit XML parsing with junitparser

Files changed:
- src/gd_tools/test_runner.py: Added parse_junit_xml() function + JUnitXml/GdToolsError imports
- tests/unit/test_test_runner.py: Added 5 tests for parse_junit_xml + updated imports
- tests/fixtures/junit/sample_results.xml: New fixture with pass/fail/skip test cases

Key decisions:
- Used JUnitXml.fromfile() for file parsing (not .parse() which doesn't exist)
- Counts totals from individual test cases rather than suite-level attributes for accuracy
- Treats both is_failure and is_error as status='fail' (JUnit XML distinguishes assertion failures vs errors)
- Uses tc.classname for suite name (falls back to suite.name if classname is None)
- Handles tc.time=None by defaulting to 0.0
- Handles tc.result being empty or message being None by defaulting to empty string
- Catches broad Exception for XML parsing errors (malformed XML can fail in many ways)
- Checks file existence before parsing for clear error messages

